SIMPLE: drumhead
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Drumhead
<hw>Drum"head`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
parchment or skin stretched over one end of a drum.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The top of a capstan which is pierced with sockets
for levers used in turning it. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Capstan</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Drumhead court-martial</b></col> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>, <cd>a
summary court-martial called to try offenses on the battlefield or the
line of march, when, sometimes, a drumhead has to do service as a
writing table.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Drumlin</ent>⟦br⟧
